  {
    "problem_id": "119",
    "problem_text_cn": "【例题 5-8】 在足够长的平直轨道上有两个小球 1 和 2, 轨道右端有一堵与轨道垂直的竖直墙, 墙面与小球轨道垂直, 如图 5-例 8 所示。设 1 和 2 两球质量分别为 $m_1$ 和 $m_2$, 初始时刻 2 处于静止, 球 1 以速度 $v$ 朝球 2 运动, 并相碰。试问两球之间且仅能发生两次碰撞时, 两球质量比 $m_2/m_1$ 的取值范围。假设球与球之间、球与墙之间的碰撞均是弹性碰撞, 且与轨道间摩擦力可略。",
    "problem_text_en": "【Example 5-8】 Two small balls, 1 and 2, are on a long straight track. At the right end of the track is a vertical wall perpendicular to the track, as shown in Fig. 5-Ex 8. The masses of the balls are $m_1$ and $m_2$ respectively. Initially, ball 2 is at rest, and ball 1 moves toward ball 2 with velocity $v$. Find the range of the mass ratio $m_2/m_1$ such that exactly two collisions occur between the two balls. Assume all collisions (ball-ball and ball-wall) are perfectly elastic and friction is negligible.",
    "problem_img": ["119_1.png"],
    "problem_img_process": [],
    "problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】 取轨道向右为 $x$ 轴正向。第一次碰撞后两球速度为 $v'_1, v'_2$。由弹性碰撞公式得:\n$v'_1 = \\frac{m_1 - m_2}{m_1 + m_2}v$, $v'_2 = \\frac{2m_1}{m_1 + m_2}v$。\n若轨道右端没有墙, 将不再碰撞。现球 2 与墙相碰, 速度变为 $-v'_2$, 两球可能发生第 2 次碰撞。发生第 2 次碰撞的条件为 $v'_1 > -v'_2$, 解得 $\\frac{m_2}{m_1} < 3$。\n第 2 次碰撞后两球速度为 $v''_1, v''_2$, 其中 $v''_2 = \\frac{4m_1(m_1 - m_2)}{(m_1 + m_2)^2}v$。\n若 $v''_2 \\le 0$, 则球 1 和球 2 向左运动, 不再发生第 3 次碰撞, 条件为 $m_2 \\ge m_1$。\n若 $v''_2 > 0$, 球 2 将与墙碰后反弹速度为 $-v''_2$, 若要不发生第 3 次碰撞, 应满足 $v''_1 \\le -v''_2$。解得 $m_2/m_1 \\ge 5 - 2\\sqrt{5}$。\n综合上述条件, 得 $5 - 2\\sqrt{5} \\le \\frac{m_2}{m_1} < 3$。",
    "problem_solution_en": "【Analysis & Solution】 Let the track be the $x$-axis. After the 1st collision, velocities are $v'_1, v'_2$. Ball 2 hits the wall and returns with $-v'_2$. A 2nd collision occurs if $v'_1 > -v'_2$, implying $m_2/m_1 < 3$. After the 2nd collision, velocities are $v''_1, v''_2$. If $v''_2 \le 0$, ball 2 moves left and won't hit the wall again, requiring $m_2 \ge m_1$. If $v''_2 > 0$, ball 2 hits the wall and returns with $-v''_2$. To prevent a 3rd collision, $v''_1 \le -v''_2$ must hold, which gives $m_2/m_1 \ge 5 - 2\\sqrt{5}$. Combining these conditions yields $5 - 2\\sqrt{5} \\le m_2/m_1 < 3$.",
