"img_cn": ["质点匀速直线运动与点$o$的位置关系示意图，标注距离$x$、速度$v$。"],
"img_en": ["Schematic diagram of the positional relationship between a particle moving uniformly in a straight line and point $o$, labeled with distance $x$ and velocity $v$."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】选择$o$点与运动直线构成的平面，质点在此平面内运动，所以质点相对于$o$点的角动量只有垂直于此平面的分量。再利用式(6.9)，写出质点运动角动量$l=p\\cdot$动量臂$=mv\\cdot x$。\n\n**说明** 1) 角动量的大小和方向与所选点$o$的位置有关。若$o$点与运动直线组成的平面不变，$x$取不同值，角动量数值将不同（角动量方向不变）；若$o$点与运动直线的距离不变，但处在过运动直线的不同平面内，则角动量的方向改变（角动量大小未变）。\n2) 质点在运动中所受合外力为零，作匀速直线运动，合外力矩必为零。在$o$点选定条件下，角动量是一个守恒量。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Choose the plane formed by point $o$ and the line of motion. Since the particle moves in this plane, its angular momentum relative to $o$ has only a component perpendicular to this plane. Using equation (6.9), the angular momentum of the particle is $l=p\\cdot$moment arm$=mv\\cdot x$.\n\n**Note** 1) The magnitude and direction of angular momentum depend on the position of the chosen point $o$. If the plane formed by $o$ and the line of motion remains unchanged but $x$ varies, the magnitude of angular momentum changes (direction remains unchanged); if the distance from $o$ to the line of motion is unchanged but $o$ lies in a different plane passing through the line of motion, the direction of angular momentum changes (magnitude remains unchanged).\n2) The net force on the particle is zero during motion, so it moves uniformly in a straight line, and the net torque must be zero. Under the condition that point $o$ is fixed, angular momentum is a conserved quantity.",
"problem_answer": "质点相对于$o$点的角动量为$l=mvx$（方向垂直于$o$点与运动直线构成的平面）。",
"difficulty": "2",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}

{
"problem_id": "124",
"problem_text_cn": "【124】一个圆锥摆，长为$L$的绳的一端悬挂在$B$点，另一端系一质量为$M$的摆球（作为质点），摆球以匀角速度$\\omega$作稳定的水平圆周运动。设圆周运动半径为$r$，圆心为$A$点。如图124_1所示。试求：1)相对于$A$点和$B$点的角动量；2)相对于$A$点和$B$点的力矩。",
"problem_text_en": "[124] A conical pendulum consists of a string of length $L$ suspended from point $B$, with a bob of mass $M$ (treated as a particle) at the other end. The bob moves in a stable horizontal circular path with angular velocity $\\omega$, radius $r$, and center at point $A$, as shown in Figure 124_1. Find: 1) The angular momentum relative to points $A$ and $B$; 2) The torque relative to points $A$ and $B$.",
"problem_img": ["124_1.png", "124_2.png", "124_3.png", "124_4.png", "124_5.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["124_6.png"],
"img_cn": ["圆锥摆结构示意图（图124_1）；绳在不同位置时角动量方向示意图（图124_2）；角动量锥面示意图（图124_3）；受力分析图（图124_4）；力矩分析图（图124_5）。"],
"img_en": ["Schematic diagram of the conical pendulum structure (Figure 124_1); angular momentum direction for different string positions (Figure 124_2); cone surface of angular momentum (Figure 124_3); force analysis diagram (Figure 124_4); torque analysis diagram (Figure 124_5)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】1) 因小球绕$A$点作速度大小$v=r\\omega$不变的匀速圆周运动，并注意到$A$点与质点运动速度始终处于同一平面内，因此，角动量方向始终只有垂直于圆平面的分量，即方向保持不变。由逆时针转动方向为正向，并用右手法则确定由$A$指向$B$为正方向。角动量大小依式(6.9)为$l_A=Mvr=Mr^2\\omega$。小球在运动中$l_A$大小也保持不变，则小球的运动相对于$A$点角动量守恒。\n\n相对于$B$点，由于$B$点与小球的速度组成的平面不断变化，所以相对于$B$点的角动量方向也不断变化。如图124_2所示，设绳在$L_1$位置，小球速度指向纸面内，相对于$B$点的转动效应按右手法则角动量所指方向为$l_{B1}$。同理绳在$L_2$位置，小球速度指向纸面外，相对于$B$点的转动效应按右手法则角动量所指方向为$l_{B2}$。小球作一个圆周运动，角动量正好画出一个锥面，如图124_3所示。\n\n小球运动相对于$B$点的角动量大小为$l_B=p\\cdot$动量臂$=MvL=MLr\\omega$。\n\n2) 小球在运动中所受到的力有重力$Mg$和绳中张力$T$，由于小球在水平面内作圆运动，所以竖直方向合力为零，即$T\\cos\\theta=Mg$。且合力指向圆心$A$。因此，相对于$A$点的力矩为零。如图124_4所示。这与小球运动相对于$A$点角动量守恒相符。\n\n相对于$B$点，由于小球受到的合力$F$指向$A$点，且$F=T\\sin\\theta=Mg\\tan\\theta$。力$F$相对于$B$点的力矩大小为$\\tau=F\\cdot$力臂$=Mg\\tan\\theta\\cdot L\\cos\\theta=MgL\\sin\\theta$，其方向必垂直于$F$与$B$点组成的平面（因为只有垂直于此平面的力矩分量）。如图124_5所示。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] 1) The bob moves in a uniform circular motion around point $A$ with constant speed $v=r\\omega$. Since point $A$ and the particle's velocity always lie in the same plane, the angular momentum has only a component perpendicular to the circular plane, so its direction remains unchanged. Taking the counterclockwise direction as positive and using the right-hand rule to define the positive direction from $A$ to $B$, the angular momentum magnitude is $l_A=Mvr=Mr^2\\omega$. The magnitude of $l_A$ remains constant during motion, so angular momentum is conserved relative to point $A$.\n\nRelative to point $B$, the plane formed by $B$ and the bob's velocity continuously changes, so the direction of angular momentum relative to $B$ also changes continuously. As shown in Figure 124_2, when the string is at position $L_1$, the bob's velocity points into the paper, and the angular momentum direction (by the right-hand rule) is $l_{B1}$. When the string is at position $L_2$, the velocity points out of the paper, and the angular momentum direction is $l_{B2}$. As the bob completes one revolution, the angular momentum traces a cone, as shown in Figure 124_3.\n\nThe magnitude of angular momentum relative to $B$ is $l_B=p\\cdot$moment arm$=MvL=MLr\\omega$.\n\n2) The forces acting on the bob are gravity $Mg$ and tension $T$. Since the bob moves in a horizontal circle, the vertical force balance gives $T\\cos\\theta=Mg$. The net force points to the center $A$, so the torque relative to $A$ is zero, consistent with angular momentum conservation about $A$.\n\nRelative to $B$, the net force $F=T\\sin\\theta=Mg\\tan\\theta$ points to $A$. The torque magnitude about $B$ is $\\tau=F\\cdot$moment arm$=Mg\\tan\\theta\\cdot L\\cos\\theta=MgL\\sin\\theta$, directed perpendicular to the plane formed by $F$ and $B$.",
"problem_answer": "1) 相对于$A$点的角动量：$l_A=Mr^2\\omega$（方向垂直圆平面向上）；相对于$B$点的角动量：$l_B=MLr\\omega$（方向随时间变化，轨迹为锥面）。\n2) 相对于$A$点的力矩：$\\tau_A=0$；相对于$B$点的力矩：$\\tau_B=MgL\\sin\\theta$（方向垂直于$F$与$B$点组成的平面）。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics",]
}

{
"problem_id": "125",
"problem_text_cn": "【125】蟹状星云中心的脉冲星PS0531的电磁脉冲周期为0.0331秒，即每秒约30次。若设想这是周期星体自转的周期，那么这样一个庞大的星球如此快地转动，离心力不会把它撕裂吗？设白矮星的密度$\\rho_1\\leqslant10^8$克/厘米³，中子星的密度$\\rho_2\\approx10^{14}$克/厘米³，不被撕裂的条件下，这颗脉冲星更可能是白矮星，还是中子星？",
"problem_text_en": "[125] The electromagnetic pulse period of the pulsar PS0531 at the center of the Crab Nebula is 0.0331 seconds, approximately 30 times per second. If we assume this is the period of the star's rotation, would such a massive star be torn apart by centrifugal force due to its rapid rotation? Given that the density of a white dwarf is $\\rho_1\\leqslant10^8\\text{ g/cm}^3$ and that of a neutron star is $\\rho_2\\approx10^{14}\\text{ g/cm}^3$, which type of star is this pulsar more likely to be under the condition of not being torn apart?",
"problem_img": ["125_1.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["125_2.png"],
"img_cn": ["脉冲星自转稳定性分析示意图（图125_1）。"],
"img_en": ["Schematic diagram of rotational stability analysis for a pulsar (Figure 125_1)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】阻止星球瓦解的力只有万有引力，不瓦解的条件是在赤道表面物质满足$\\dfrac{GM}{R^2}>R\\omega^2$。代入$M=\\dfrac{4}{3}\\pi R^3\\rho$，写出密度表达式$\\rho>\\dfrac{3\\omega^2}{4\\pi G}$。其中$\\omega=2\\pi f=2\\pi\\times30$（秒⁻¹），解得密度的下限$\\rho_0=\\dfrac{3\\omega^2}{4\\pi G}\\approx1.3\\times10^{11}$（克/厘米³）。此结果有$\\rho_0>\\rho_1$，$\\rho_0<\\rho_2$，所以此不被撕裂的脉冲星不可能是白矮星，只能是中子星。经证实脉冲星就是高速旋转的中子星。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] The only force preventing the star from disintegrating is gravitational force. The condition for stability is that the gravitational acceleration at the equator exceeds the centrifugal acceleration: $\\dfrac{GM}{R^2}>R\\omega^2$. Substituting $M=\\dfrac{4}{3}\\pi R^3\\rho$, we derive the density condition $\\rho>\\dfrac{3\\omega^2}{4\\pi G}$. With $\\omega=2\\pi f=2\\pi\\times30\\text{ rad/s}$, the minimum density is $\\rho_0=\\dfrac{3\\omega^2}{4\\pi G}\\approx1.3\\times10^{11}\\text{ g/cm}^3$. Since $\\rho_0>\\rho_1$ and $\\rho_0<\\rho_2$, the pulsar cannot be a white dwarf and must be a neutron star. Pulsars are indeed rapidly rotating neutron stars.",
"problem_answer": "不被撕裂的密度下限约为$1.3\\times10^{11}\\text{ g/cm}^3$，因此这颗脉冲星更可能是中子星。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics" ]
}

{
"problem_id": "126",
"problem_text_cn": "【126】如图126_1所示，$CD$、$EF$为长度等于$2l$的轻质刚性杆，其端点均固连一质量为$m$的质点。$CE$、$DF$为长度等于$l$的不可伸长的细线。$CD$杆中点$B$用一细线悬于天花板$A$点。突然剪断细线$DF$，求剪断后瞬时，细线$AB$中的张力。",
"problem_text_en": "[126] As shown in Figure 126_1, $CD$ and $EF$ are light rigid rods of length $2l$, each with a particle of mass $m$ fixed at their endpoints. $CE$ and $DF$ are inextensible strings of length $l$. The midpoint $B$ of rod $CD$ is suspended from the ceiling at point $A$ by a string. The string $DF$ is suddenly cut. Find the tension in string $AB$ immediately after the cut.",
"problem_img": ["126_1.png", "126_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["126_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["初始结构示意图（图126_1）；剪断后受力分析图（图126_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Initial structure diagram (Figure 126_1); force analysis diagram after cutting (Figure 126_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】剪断线$DF$后瞬间，设绳$AB$中张力$T'$，绳$CE$中张力$T$，如图126_2所示。\n\n刚剪断$DF$，杆$EF$对质点$E$无竖直作用力，所以质点$E$在竖直方向的动力学方程写为（竖直向下为正）$mg-T=ma$ ①，其中$a$为质点$E$的竖直向下加速度。\n\n再以$CD$杆作为研究对象。在刚剪断$DF$时，$CD$杆绕$B$点转动，相对于过$B$点垂直纸面的轴，$T'$的力矩为零，作用在质点$C$上的张力$T$对$B$轴的力矩为$M=Tl$。此力矩等于由质点$C$和$D$组成的系统的总角动量的时间变化率（即质点系角动量定律），即$Tl=\\dfrac{\\Delta(m lv+mlv)}{\\Delta t}=2mla$ ②。\n\n联立式①和②，解得$T=\\dfrac{2}{3}mg$。\n\n再利用$C$和$D$两质点系统在竖直方向的质心静止，即方程$T'=T+2mg=\\dfrac{8}{3}mg$。这就是绳$AB$中的张力。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Immediately after cutting string $DF$, let the tension in $AB$ be $T'$ and the tension in $CE$ be $T$, as shown in Figure 126_2.\n\nJust after cutting $DF$, rod $EF$ exerts no vertical force on particle $E$, so the vertical dynamic equation for $E$ (downward as positive) is $mg-T=ma$ ①, where $a$ is the downward acceleration of $E$.\n\nTaking rod $CD$ as the object of study, it rotates about point $B$ immediately after the cut. The tension $T'$ exerts no torque about the axis through $B$ (perpendicular to the paper), while the tension $T$ at $C$ exerts a torque $M=Tl$. By the angular momentum theorem for the system of particles $C$ and $D$, this torque equals the rate of change of angular momentum: $Tl=\\dfrac{\\Delta(m lv+mlv)}{\\Delta t}=2mla$ ②.\n\nSolving equations ① and ② gives $T=\\dfrac{2}{3}mg$.\n\nUsing the condition that the center of mass of particles $C$ and $D$ is stationary vertically, we have $T'=T+2mg=\\dfrac{8}{3}mg$, which is the tension in string $AB$.",
"problem_answer": "剪断后瞬间，细线$AB$中的张力为$T'=\\dfrac{8}{3}mg$。",
"difficulty": "4",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics", ]
}

{
"problem_id": "127",
"problem_text_cn": "【127】质量均为$m$的三个小球置于光滑水平桌面上，并用长为$l$的轻质刚性杆$AB$、$BC$光滑连接，$\\angle ABC=\\pi-\\alpha$（$\\alpha<\\pi/2$）。已知整个系统在桌面上以速度$V$沿$AB$方向运动，如图127_1所示。当小球$C$与桌上垂直于$AB$的竖直、光滑、完全非弹性固定壁相碰时，此壁将受到一个冲量。试证此冲量值为$mV(3+\\sin^2\\alpha)/(1+3\\sin^2\\alpha)$。",
"problem_text_en": "[127] Three balls of mass $m$ are placed on a smooth horizontal table and connected by light rigid rods $AB$ and $BC$ of length $l$, with $\\angle ABC=\\pi-\\alpha$ ($\\alpha<\\pi/2$). The entire system moves along the $AB$ direction at speed $V$, as shown in Figure 127_1. When ball $C$ collides with a vertical, smooth, perfectly inelastic fixed wall perpendicular to $AB$ on the table, the wall receives an impulse. Prove that the impulse magnitude is $mV(3+\\sin^2\\alpha)/(1+3\\sin^2\\alpha)$.",
"problem_img": ["127_1.png", "127_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["127_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["系统初始运动示意图（图127_1）；碰撞后速度分析图（图127_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Initial motion diagram of the system (Figure 127_1); velocity analysis diagram after collision (Figure 127_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】设此系统与固定壁相碰后瞬时三个小球的速度示于图127_2中，设壁受到的冲量值为$I$，则壁对系统的反作用冲量值也为$I$。写出垂直于壁面和平行于壁面两方向系统满足的动量定理：\n$I=-m(u+u)-m(-V-V-V)=m(3V-2u)$ ①\n$mv_1=mv_2$ ②\n\n$A$和$B$两质点运动中距离不变，已在图127_2中设定$AB$方向速度为$u$而得到满足。$B$和$C$两质点运动中距离保持不变，有关系$v_2\\sin\\alpha=u\\cos\\alpha-v_1\\sin\\alpha$ ③。\n\n上述三个方程，有四个未知量$I$、$u$、$v_1$、$v_2$。再找一个方程。由于碰撞中壁对系统的冲量作用点在$C$点，所以碰撞中相对于$C$点的轴的冲量矩为零。因此，碰撞前后，系统相对于$C$轴（过$C$点垂直桌面）角动量守恒，即$2mu\\cdot l\\sin\\alpha+mv_1l\\cos\\alpha=2mVl\\sin\\alpha$ ④。\n\n联立上述四个方程，消去$u$、$v_1$、$v_2$，解得：$I=mV\\dfrac{3+\\sin^2\\alpha}{1+3\\sin^2\\alpha}$。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Let the velocities of the three balls immediately after the collision be as shown in Figure 127_2. Let the impulse received by the wall be $I$, so the reaction impulse on the system is also $I$. Applying the momentum theorem perpendicular and parallel to the wall:\n$I=-m(u+u)-m(-V-V-V)=m(3V-2u)$ ①\n$mv_1=mv_2$ ②\n\nThe distance between $A$ and $B$ remains constant, so their velocity component along $AB$ is $u$. The distance between $B$ and $C$ remains constant, giving $v_2\\sin\\alpha=u\\cos\\alpha-v_1\\sin\\alpha$ ③.\n\nThere are four unknowns ($I$, $u$, $v_1$, $v_2$) and three equations. Since the impulse acts at $C$, the angular momentum about the axis through $C$ (perpendicular to the table) is conserved: $2mu\\cdot l\\sin\\alpha+mv_1l\\cos\\alpha=2mVl\\sin\\alpha$ ④.\n\nSolving the four equations simultaneously gives $I=mV\\dfrac{3+\\sin^2\\alpha}{1+3\\sin^2\\alpha}$.",
"problem_answer": "壁受到的冲量值为$I=mV\\dfrac{3+\\sin^2\\alpha}{1+3\\sin^2\\alpha}$。",
"difficulty": "4",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics", ]
}
{
"problem_id": "128",
"problem_text_cn": "【128】直到牛顿最终得到万有引力定律表达式之前，人们已经认识到，物体之间存在引力的观念，太阳的引力决定了行星运动的观念。进一步，牛顿认为物体间的引力是万有的、普适的、统一的，即一切物体之间都存在这种引力作用，称为万有引力。牛顿指出，地上物体的运动规律与天上月亮运动的规律实质上是一样的。这个结论纠正了亚里士多德关于天上运动和地面运动是本质不同的两类运动的错误观念。假设月亮绕地球运动轨道是一个圆轨道，试利用开普勒定律（即第二、第三定律）导出牛顿万有引力定律。",
"problem_text_en": "[128] Before Newton finally derived the expression for the law of universal gravitation, it was already recognized that there is a gravitational force between objects, and that the Sun's gravitational force determines the motion of planets. Furthermore, Newton proposed that the gravitational force between objects is universal, pervasive, and unified—existing between all objects, hence called universal gravitation. Newton pointed out that the laws governing the motion of objects on Earth are essentially the same as those governing the motion of the Moon in the sky, correcting Aristotle's erroneous view that celestial and terrestrial motions are fundamentally different. Assuming the Moon orbits the Earth in a circular path, derive Newton's law of universal gravitation using Kepler's laws (the second and third laws).",
"problem_img": ["128_1.png", "128_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["128_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["推导万有引力定律的过程示意图（图128_1）；万有引力定律的最终表达式（图128_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Schematic diagram of the derivation of the law of universal gravitation (Figure 128_1); final expression of the law of universal gravitation (Figure 128_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】由于地球质量远大于月亮质量，暂且认为地球不动，月亮绕地球作圆周运动。根据开普勒第二定律，月亮必作匀速圆周运动，向心加速度$a$为$a = \\dfrac{v^2}{r}$，其中$v$是月亮的速率，$r$是圆轨道半径。根据开普勒第三定律，月亮运动周期$T$满足$T \\propto r^{3/2}$。又注意到$v = \\dfrac{2\\pi r}{T}$，所以$v \\propto \\dfrac{r}{r^{3/2}} = \\dfrac{1}{r^{1/2}}$。代入向心加速度表达式，得$a \\propto \\dfrac{1}{r^2}$，或$F = m_月 a \\propto \\dfrac{m_月}{r^2}$。其中$m_月$是月亮的质量。取比例系数为$k$，写成等式$F = m_月 \\dfrac{k}{r^2} = F_{地→月}$。显然，$k$应取决于地球的性质，$F_{地→月}$指地球对月亮的引力。\n\n根据万有引力的普适性，月亮对地球的引力应当有如下形式$F_{月→地} = m_地 \\dfrac{k'}{r^2}$，其中$k'$取决于月亮的性质。再根据牛顿第三定律，$F_{地→月}$与$F_{月→地}$大小相等，即$k/k' = m_地/m_月$。因此，$k = Gm_地$，$k' = Gm_月$。两式（$F_{地→月}$和$F_{月→地}$）统一写为$F = G\\dfrac{m_地 m_月}{r^2}$。\n\n利用牛顿提出的引力的普适性，任何具有质量$m_1$和$m_2$、相距$r$的两质点之间的引力，总是沿着两质点连线方向，其大小为$F = G\\dfrac{m_1 m_2}{r^2}$。式中$G$是对所有质点都具有相同数值的普适常数（万有引力常数）。这就是牛顿万有引力定律。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Since the Earth's mass is much larger than the Moon's, we assume the Earth is stationary and the Moon orbits it in a circle. By Kepler's second law, the Moon moves with uniform circular motion, so its centripetal acceleration is $a = \\dfrac{v^2}{r}$, where $v$ is the Moon's speed and $r$ is the orbital radius. By Kepler's third law, the orbital period $T$ satisfies $T \\propto r^{3/2}$. Using $v = \\dfrac{2\\pi r}{T}$, we find $v \\propto \\dfrac{1}{r^{1/2}}$, so the acceleration is $a \\propto \\dfrac{1}{r^2}$. The gravitational force is thus $F = m_月 a \\propto \\dfrac{m_月}{r^2}$. Letting the proportionality constant be $k$, we write $F = m_月 \\dfrac{k}{r^2} = F_{Earth→Moon}$, where $k$ depends on the Earth's properties.\n\nBy the universality of gravitation, the force exerted by the Moon on the Earth is $F_{Moon→Earth} = m_地 \\dfrac{k'}{r^2}$, with $k'$ depending on the Moon's properties. By Newton's third law, $F_{Earth→Moon} = F_{Moon→Earth}$, so $k/k' = m_地/m_月$. Setting $k = Gm_地$ and $k' = Gm_月$, we unify the expressions to $F = G\\dfrac{m_地 m_月}{r^2}$.\n\nGeneralizing, the gravitational force between any two masses $m_1$ and $m_2$ separated by $r$ is $F = G\\dfrac{m_1 m_2}{r^2}$, where $G$ is the universal gravitational constant. This is Newton's law of universal gravitation.",
"problem_answer": "牛顿万有引力定律为$F = G\\dfrac{m_1 m_2}{r^2}$，其中$G$为万有引力常数。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics", ,]
}

{
"problem_id": "129",
"problem_text_cn": "【129】牛顿证明了：一个质量均匀分布的球壁状物质层，对放在其内部区域的质点不产生重力作用（即质点受此均匀球壁状物质层引力的合力为零），而对放置在其外部的质点则产生引力作用，而且其作用就像是整个球壁层的质量都集中在它的几何中心一样。由此结论还可推得：一个质量球对称分布的球形物体（质量均匀分布的球体是其中一特例），对放在其内部离球心距离为$r$（$r$小于球半径）的质点的重力作用等于球体中离球心相距$r$的球体内的质量对质点的合引力作用，而其作用就像是半径为$r$的球的那部分质量都集中在它的几何中心一样。离球心相距大于$r$的球体内的质量对质点的合引力作用为零。对放置在整个球外部的质点产生的引力作用就像是整个球体的质量集中在它的几何中心一样。我们在此要求证明质量均匀分布的球壁状物质层对放置在球内任一点处的质点的合引力为零。如图129_1所示，质量为$M$、半径为$R$的匀质薄球壳内任意一点$P$处有一点质量$m$。以$P$为顶点作两对顶的很小的圆锥，它们在球壳面上分别截得很小的面积$\\Delta A_1$、$\\Delta A_2$。试证：1)两小面积元$\\Delta A_1$、$\\Delta A_2$的质量元对$P$点处点质量$m$所施引力之和为零；2)整个球壳对壳内任意一点处的质点的合引力为零（牛顿方法）；3)求匀质球体（质量为$M$、半径为$R$）对球内离球心$r$（$r<R$）处的点质量$m$的引力大小。",
"problem_text_en": "[129] Newton proved that a uniformly spherical shell exerts no net gravitational force on a particle inside it, while acting as if all its mass were concentrated at its center for a particle outside. This implies that a spherically symmetric mass distribution (e.g., a uniform sphere) exerts a force on an internal particle at distance $r$ from the center equal to that of a sphere of radius $r$, with the outer mass contributing nothing. Prove that a uniform spherical shell exerts zero net force on an internal particle. As shown in Figure 129_1, a point mass $m$ is at point $P$ inside a uniform thin spherical shell of mass $M$ and radius $R$. Two small, opposite cones with vertex at $P$ cut out small areas $\\Delta A_1$ and $\\Delta A_2$ on the shell. Prove: 1) The gravitational forces from $\\Delta A_1$ and $\\Delta A_2$ on $m$ sum to zero; 2) The total force on $m$ from the entire shell is zero (Newton's method); 3) Find the gravitational force on $m$ inside a uniform sphere of mass $M$ and radius $R$ at distance $r < R$ from the center.",
"problem_img": ["129_1.png", "129_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["129_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["匀质薄球壳内引力分析示意图（图129_1）；引力推导过程（图129_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Schematic diagram of gravitational analysis inside a uniform spherical shell (Figure 129_1); derivation of gravitational force (Figure 129_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】1) 设对顶小圆锥在薄球壳上截得的小面元离$P$点的距离分别为$r_1$、$r_2$（由于面元很小，$\\Delta A_1$上任一点离$P$点距离可以认为都是$r_1$；小面元$\\Delta A_2$也类似）；令小面元的外法向为其方向。过小面元$\\Delta A_1$、$\\Delta A_2$中心、球心$o$作一平面，与薄球壳截得半径为$R$的大圆，$r_1$、$r_2$必在此圆面上。小面元$\\Delta A_1$、$\\Delta A_2$的外法向都是球的径向，它们与$r_1$、$r_2$的夹角相等，设为$\\varphi$；过$\\Delta A_1$中心作一垂直于$r_1$的截面（法向与$r_1$一致），截小圆锥得小面元$\\Delta A_1'$，同样，过$\\Delta A_2$中心截得小面元$\\Delta A_2'$，有关系$\\dfrac{\\Delta A_1'}{\\Delta A_2'} = \\dfrac{r_1^2}{r_2^2}$ ①。又因为$\\Delta A_1 = \\dfrac{\\Delta A_1'}{\\cos\\varphi}$，$\\Delta A_2 = \\dfrac{\\Delta A_2'}{\\cos\\varphi}$ ②，代入式①得$\\dfrac{\\Delta A_1}{\\Delta A_2} = \\dfrac{r_1^2}{r_2^2}$ ③。因匀质薄球壳有$\\dfrac{\\Delta m_1}{\\Delta m_2} = \\dfrac{\\Delta A_1}{\\Delta A_2}$ ④，所以$\\dfrac{\\Delta m_1}{\\Delta m_2} = \\dfrac{r_1^2}{r_2^2}$ ⑤。两面元的质量$\\Delta m_1$、$\\Delta m_2$对$P$点质量$m$的引力分别为$f_1 = \\dfrac{G\\Delta m_1 \\cdot m}{r_1^2}$，$f_2 = \\dfrac{G\\Delta m_2 \\cdot m}{r_2^2}$。利用式⑤得$f_1 = f_2$，而方向相反，所以合引力为零。\n\n2) 过$P$点作许多对顶小圆锥，把匀质薄球壳分成许多对$\\Delta A_1$、$\\Delta A_2$（全部分完），每一对质量元对点质量$m$的合引力都为零，所以整个薄球壳对$P$点处的点质量$m$的合引力为零。由于$P$点在薄球壳内是任意选取的，所以不管质量为$m$的质点放在球内何处，结论相同，即匀质薄球壳内任意一点引力场强均为零。\n\n3) 设匀质球体内有一质点，质量为$m$，离球心距离为$r$。设想，球体内离球心大于$r$部分分成许许多多很薄的匀质薄球壳，而每个匀质薄球壳对$r$处的点质量$m$的合引力为零。所以匀质球体内离球心大于$r$部分对$r$处点质量的合引力为零。而球体内离球心小于$r$部分可以等价于球心处的一个质量为$M\\dfrac{r^3}{R^3}$的质点对$m$产生的引力，其大小为$f = \\dfrac{GMm r}{R^3}$。这个力与$r$成正比，指向球心。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] 1) Let the small surface elements $\\Delta A_1$ and $\\Delta A_2$ be at distances $r_1$ and $r_2$ from $P$. The cones subtend these elements, which are small enough that all points on $\\Delta A_1$ are approximately at $r_1$ and similarly for $\\Delta A_2$. The normals to $\\Delta A_1$ and $\\Delta A_2$ are radial, making equal angles $\\varphi$ with $r_1$ and $r_2$. Projecting these elements onto planes perpendicular to $r_1$ and $r_2$ gives $\\dfrac{\\Delta A_1'}{\\Delta A_2'} = \\dfrac{r_1^2}{r_2^2}$. Since $\\Delta A_1 = \\dfrac{\\Delta A_1'}{\\cos\\varphi}$ and $\\Delta A_2 = \\dfrac{\\Delta A_2'}{\\cos\\varphi}$, we find $\\dfrac{\\Delta A_1}{\\Delta A_2} = \\dfrac{r_1^2}{r_2^2}$. For a uniform shell, $\\dfrac{\\Delta m_1}{\\Delta m_2} = \\dfrac{\\Delta A_1}{\\Delta A_2}$, so $\\dfrac{\\Delta m_1}{\\Delta m_2} = \\dfrac{r_1^2}{r_2^2}$. The gravitational forces are $f_1 = \\dfrac{G\\Delta m_1 m}{r_1^2}$ and $f_2 = \\dfrac{G\\Delta m_2 m}{r_2^2}$, which are equal in magnitude and opposite in direction, summing to zero.\n\n2) Covering the shell with such pairs of cones shows that the total force on $m$ is zero, as each pair cancels out. Since $P$ is arbitrary, the gravitational field inside a uniform spherical shell is zero.\n\n3) For a uniform sphere, the mass inside radius $r$ is $M\\dfrac{r^3}{R^3}$. The force on $m$ at distance $r$ from the center is $f = \\dfrac{GMm r}{R^3}$, proportional to $r$ and directed inward.",
"problem_answer": "1) 两小面积元对$P$点质量的引力大小相等、方向相反，合力为零；\n2) 整个球壳对内部质点的合引力为零；\n3) 匀质球体对内部质点的引力为$f = \\dfrac{GMm r}{R^3}$。",
"difficulty": "4",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics" ]
}

{
"problem_id": "130",
"problem_text_cn": "【130】从地球表面向火星发射火星探测器。设地球和火星都在同一平面上绕太阳作圆周运动。火星轨道半径$R_m$为地球轨道半径$R_0$的1.500倍。简单而又比较节省能量的发射过程可分为两步进行：第一步，在地球表面用火箭对探测器进行加速，使之获得足够的动能，从而脱离地球引力作用成为一个沿地球轨道运行的人造卫星。第二步是在适当时刻点燃与探测器连在一起的火箭发动机，在短时间内对探测器沿原方向加速，使其速度数值增加到适当值，从而使得探测器沿着一个与地球轨道及火星轨道分别在长轴两端相切的半个椭圆轨道射到火星上，如图130_1(a)所示。问：1)为使探测器成为沿地球轨道运行的人造卫星，必须加速探测器，使之在地面附近获得多大的速度（相对于地球）？2)当探测器脱离地球并沿地球公转轨道稳定运行后，在某年3月1日零时测得探测器与火星之间的角距离为$60^\\circ$，如图130_1(b)所示。问应在何年何月何日点燃探测器上的火箭发动机方能使探测器恰好落在火星表面？（时间计算仅需精确到日）已知地球半径$R_e = 6.4 \\times 10^6 \\text{ m}$，重力加速度$g$可取$9.8 \\text{ m/s}^2$。",
"problem_text_en": "[130] A Mars probe is launched from Earth's surface. Assume Earth and Mars orbit the Sun in the same plane, with Mars' orbital radius $R_m = 1.500 R_0$ (where $R_0$ is Earth's orbital radius). The energy-efficient launch has two stages: (1) Accelerate the probe from Earth's surface to escape Earth's gravity and enter Earth's orbit around the Sun. (2) At the right moment, ignite the probe's rocket to increase its speed, placing it into a half-elliptical transfer orbit tangent to both Earth's and Mars' orbits, as shown in Figure 130_1(a). Questions: 1) What speed (relative to Earth) must the probe achieve near the surface to escape Earth and enter its solar orbit? 2) After the probe stabilizes in Earth's orbit, the angular separation between the probe and Mars is $60^\\circ$ at 0:00 on March 1. On what date should the rocket be ignited to ensure the probe arrives at Mars? (Round to the nearest day.) Given: Earth's radius $R_e = 6.4 \\times 10^6 \\text{ m}$, $g = 9.8 \\text{ m/s}^2$.",
"problem_img": ["130_1.png", "130_2.png", "130_3.png", "130_4.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["130_5.png"],
"img_cn": ["霍曼转移轨道示意图（图130_1）；探测器与火星的角距离示意图（图130_2）；轨道周期计算（图130_3）；等待时间推导（图130_4）。"],
"img_en": ["Hohmann transfer orbit diagram (Figure 130_1); angular separation between probe and Mars (Figure 130_2); orbital period calculation (Figure 130_3); derivation of waiting time (Figure 130_4)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】1) 当探测器脱离地球引力作用成为沿地球轨道运动的人造卫星时，可以认为探测器相对地球的速度为零，探测器以与地球相同的速度和轨道绕日作圆周运动。因此，探测器在地面附近应获得的速度为$v = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2GM_e}{R_e}} = \\sqrt{2gR_e} = 1.12 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$。这就是摆脱地球引力，地面上应具有的第二宇宙速度。\n\n2) 为使探测器沿椭圆轨道到达与火星轨道的相切点时，火星恰好运行到这一点，必须选择适当时机点燃火箭发动机。为此，需要求出几个物理量：\n\n(ⅰ) 探测器（或地球）在地球公转轨道上运动周期$T_d = T_e = 365$（天），以及对应的角速度$\\omega_d = \\omega_e = \\dfrac{360^\\circ}{365 \\text{ 天}} = 0.986^\\circ/\\text{天}$。\n\n(ⅱ) 火星公转周期$T_m = 365\\sqrt{(1.5)^3} = 365 \\times 1.84 = 671$（天），角速度$\\omega_m = 360^\\circ/671 \\text{ 天} = 0.537^\\circ/\\text{天}$。\n\n(ⅲ) 探测器在椭圆轨道上的运行周期$T_d'$。探测器的椭圆轨道半长轴为$\\dfrac{R_0 + 1.5R_0}{2} = 1.25R_0$，所以$T_d' = 365\\sqrt{(1.25)^3} = 365 \\times 1.40 = 510$（天）。因此，探测器从点燃火箭发动机至到达火星所需时间为$\\dfrac{1}{2}T_d' = 255$（天）。\n\n(ⅳ) 探测器运行至火星的255天内，火星运行的角距离为$\\omega_m \\cdot \\dfrac{1}{2}T_d' = 0.537^\\circ/\\text{天} \\times 255 \\text{ 天} = 137^\\circ$。为了使探测器到达火星轨道时，正好射到火星上，那么探测器在椭圆轨道近日点点燃火箭时，火星应在其远日点的切点之前$137^\\circ$处，也即探测器点燃发动机时，与火星的角距离应为$180^\\circ - 137^\\circ = 43^\\circ$。但是，已知某年3月1日零时探测器与火星的角距离为$60^\\circ$（火星在前，探测器在后），为使其角距离成为$43^\\circ$，必须等待一段时间，设为$t$天，使二者达到角距离$43^\\circ$的合适位置。$t$满足$60^\\circ - 43^\\circ = (\\omega_d - \\omega_m)t$，即$t = \\dfrac{60^\\circ - 43^\\circ}{0.986^\\circ/\\text{天} - 0.537^\\circ/\\text{天}} = \\dfrac{17^\\circ}{0.449^\\circ/\\text{天}} \\approx 37.8 \\approx 38$（天）。因此点燃火箭发动机的时刻应为当年的3月1日之后38天，即同年的4月7日。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] 1) To escape Earth's gravity and enter its solar orbit, the probe must reach the escape velocity from Earth: $v = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2GM_e}{R_e}} = \\sqrt{2gR_e} = 1.12 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$, which is Earth's second cosmic velocity.\n\n2) To ensure the probe arrives at Mars when Mars reaches the transfer orbit's far point, calculate the following:\n\n(ⅰ) Earth's orbital period: $T_d = T_e = 365$ days, angular velocity: $\\omega_d = \\dfrac{360^\\circ}{365} \\approx 0.986^\\circ/$day.\n\n(ⅱ) Mars' orbital period: $T_m = 365\\sqrt{1.5^3} \\approx 671$ days, angular velocity: $\\omega_m = \\dfrac{360^\\circ}{671} \\approx 0.537^\\circ/$day.\n\n(ⅲ) Transfer orbit semi-major axis: $a = 1.25R_0$, period: $T_d' = 365\\sqrt{1.25^3} \\approx 510$ days. Time to Mars: $\\dfrac{T_d'}{2} = 255$ days.\n\n(ⅳ) Mars moves $\\omega_m \\times 255 \\approx 137^\\circ$ during the transfer. The required initial angular separation is $180^\\circ - 137^\\circ = 43^\\circ$. With an initial separation of $60^\\circ$, wait $t = \\dfrac{60^\\circ - 43^\\circ}{\\omega_d - \\omega_m} \\approx 38$ days. Ignition date: March 1 + 38 days = April 7.",
"problem_answer": "1) 探测器在地面附近需获得的速度为$1.12 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$（第二宇宙速度）；\n2) 火箭发动机应在同年4月7日点燃。",
"difficulty": "4",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}

{
"problem_id": "131",
"problem_text_cn": "【131】引力半径与宇宙半径。在地球表面平抛一个物体，如果速度足够大，它将可能绕地球作圆周运动。此时的速度值被称为第一宇宙速度，其值为$v_1 = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{GM_e}{R_e}} = \\sqrt{gR_e} = \\sqrt{9.8 \\times 6400 \\times 10^3} \\approx 7.9$（千米/秒）。如果速度更大，以至此物逃离地球，不再返回，那么这个速度至少应为$v_2 = \\sqrt{2gR_e} \\approx 11.2$（千米/秒）。这个速度被称为第二宇宙速度。以上是对地球而言。对于任何一个质量为$M$，半径为$r$的均匀球形系统都有类似于地球情况下的这两个特征速度。求：1)若此球形系统的第二宇宙速度超过光速，那么$r$的最大值记为$r_g$，被称为引力半径。设地球质量为$6.0 \\times 10^{24}$千克，计算地球的引力半径$R_g$；2)若物质均匀分布于半径为$r$的球体内，质量密度为$\\rho$，总质量为$M$。且此时的$r$正好是引力半径$r_g$，写出$r_g$的表达式。设宇宙环境在大尺度上质量是均匀分布的，质量密度平均值为$10^{-29}$克/厘米³，求$r_g$。这个半径称为宇宙半径。",
"problem_text_en": "[131] Gravitational radius and cosmic radius. If an object is projected horizontally from Earth's surface with sufficient speed, it will orbit Earth in a circle; this speed is the first cosmic velocity: $v_1 = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{GM_e}{R_e}} \\approx 7.9 \\text{ km/s}$. A greater speed will allow it to escape Earth permanently, which is the second cosmic velocity: $v_2 = \\sqrt{2gR_e} \\approx 11.2 \\text{ km/s}$. These velocities apply to any uniform spherical system of mass $M$ and radius $r$. Questions: 1) If the second cosmic velocity exceeds the speed of light, the maximum radius is called the gravitational radius $r_g$. Calculate Earth's gravitational radius $R_g$ given $M = 6.0 \\times 10^{24} \\text{ kg}$. 2) For a uniform sphere of density $\\rho$ and total mass $M$, express $r_g$ when the radius equals the gravitational radius. Given the universe's average density $\\rho = 10^{-29} \\text{ g/cm}^3$, find $r_g$ (the cosmic radius).",
"problem_img": ["131_1.png", "131_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["131_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["宇宙速度与引力半径的关系（图131_1）；引力半径的推导与计算（图131_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Relationship between cosmic velocities and gravitational radius (Figure 131_1); derivation and calculation of gravitational radius (Figure 131_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】1) 由题文给出第二宇宙速度与光速的关系$\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2GM}{r}} > c$，解得$r < \\dfrac{2GM}{c^2}$。引力半径为$r_g = \\dfrac{2GM}{c^2}$。代入地球质量$M$，以及引力常数$G$和光速$c$，得$r_g \\approx 0.9$（厘米）。设想地球全部质量缩小到1厘米以下的小球内，那么外界就得不到这个地球的任何光信息，这就是黑洞。\n\n2) 由题给各物理量，总质量表为$M = \\dfrac{4}{3}\\pi r^3 \\rho$。又，$r$正好是引力半径，即$r_g = \\dfrac{2G \\cdot \\dfrac{4}{3}\\pi r_g^3 \\rho}{c^2}$，解得$r_g = \\left(\\dfrac{3c^2}{8\\pi G\\rho}\\right)^{1/2}$。用题给$\\rho$的数据代入，得到$r_g \\approx 10^{26}$（米）。我们不可能把光发射到$10^{26}$米以外的空间。这个尺度称为宇宙半径。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] 1) The second cosmic velocity exceeds the speed of light when $\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2GM}{r}} > c$, so $r < \\dfrac{2GM}{c^2}$. The gravitational radius is $r_g = \\dfrac{2GM}{c^2}$. For Earth, $r_g \\approx 0.9 \\text{ cm}$. If Earth were compressed to this size, it would become a black hole, as no light could escape.\n\n2) For a uniform sphere, $M = \\dfrac{4}{3}\\pi r^3 \\rho$. Setting $r = r_g$, we solve $r_g = \\dfrac{2G \\cdot \\dfrac{4}{3}\\pi r_g^3 \\rho}{c^2}$ to get $r_g = \\left(\\dfrac{3c^2}{8\\pi G\\rho}\\right)^{1/2}$. Substituting $\\rho = 10^{-29} \\text{ g/cm}^3$, we find $r_g \\approx 10^{26} \\text{ m}$, the cosmic radius beyond which light cannot escape.",
"problem_answer": "1) 地球的引力半径约为$0.9 \\text{ cm}$；\n2) 引力半径表达式为$r_g = \\left(\\dfrac{3c^2}{8\\pi G\\rho}\\right)^{1/2}$，宇宙半径约为$10^{26} \\text{ m}$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}
{
"problem_id": "132",
"problem_text_cn": "【132】第三宇宙速度。从地球表面以一定速度发射宇宙飞船，使它不仅能摆脱地球的引力束缚，而且能摆脱太阳的引力束缚，继而飞向太空。这一相对地球发射速度的最小值称为第三宇宙速度。求此第三宇宙速度的值。",
"problem_text_en": "[132] Third cosmic velocity. A spacecraft is launched from Earth's surface with a speed sufficient to escape both Earth's and the Sun's gravitational pull, entering interstellar space. The minimum launch speed relative to Earth is called the third cosmic velocity. Find the value of the third cosmic velocity.",
"problem_img": ["132_1.png", "132_2.png", "132_3.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["132_4.png"],
"img_cn": ["第三宇宙速度推导示意图（图132_1）；地球绕日速度与逃逸速度计算（图132_2）；椭圆轨道机械能分析（图132_3）。"],
"img_en": ["Derivation of the third cosmic velocity (Figure 132_1); calculation of Earth's orbital speed and escape velocity (Figure 132_2); mechanical energy analysis of elliptical orbits (Figure 132_3)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】设第三宇宙速度的大小为$v_3$。宇宙飞船自地球发射后，不仅能脱离地球引力，且在地球引力消失时，相对地球速度不为零，设此相对地球速度为$u$，则有能量关系：\n$$\\frac{1}{2}mv_3^2 - G\\frac{M_e m}{R_e} = \\frac{1}{2}mu^2$$\n其中$M_e$和$R_e$分别为地球质量和地球半径，$m$为飞船质量。\n\n由于地球正绕太阳运行，此处用圆轨道近似，地球绕行速度大小为：\n$$V_e = \\sqrt{\\frac{GM_\\odot}{r_e}} \\approx 3.0 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$$\n其中$M_\\odot$为太阳质量，$r_e$为地球到太阳的平均距离。\n\n为了节省能量，希望设法使$u$的方向与$V_e$的方向一致。因此，宇宙飞船相对太阳速度为$u+V_e$。为了使宇宙飞船能够脱离太阳引力束缚，此速度应满足：\n$$u+V_e = \\sqrt{\\frac{2GM_\\odot}{r_e}} \\approx 4.20 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$$\n得$u = 1.20 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$。\n\n把能量关系改写为：\n$$v_3^2 = u^2 + \\frac{2GM_e}{R_e} = u^2 + v_2^2$$\n这里已利用第二宇宙速度表达式：\n$$v_2 = \\sqrt{\\frac{2GM_e}{R_e}} = 1.12 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$$\n代入$u$和$v_2$的值，得到第三宇宙速度的大小：\n$$v_3 = 1.66 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$$\n",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Let the third cosmic velocity be $v_3$. After escaping Earth's gravity, the spacecraft has a residual speed $u$ relative to Earth, so the energy conservation equation is:\n$$\\frac{1}{2}mv_3^2 - G\\frac{M_e m}{R_e} = \\frac{1}{2}mu^2$$\nEarth's orbital speed around the Sun is $V_e \\approx 3.0 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$. To escape the Sun, the spacecraft's speed relative to the Sun must be $u+V_e = \\sqrt{\\frac{2GM_\\odot}{r_e}} \\approx 4.20 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$, giving $u = 1.20 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$. Using the second cosmic velocity $v_2 = 1.12 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$, we find:\n$$v_3^2 = u^2 + v_2^2 \\implies v_3 \\approx 1.66 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$$\n",
"problem_answer": "第三宇宙速度的值为$v_3 \\approx 1.66 \\times 10^4 \\text{ m/s}$（约$16.6 \\text{ km/s}$）。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics" ]
}

{
"problem_id": "133",
"problem_text_cn": "【133】从北极发射一导弹，落在赤道上（经历纬度90°）。求能量最省的发射速度。引力常数$G=6.67 \\times 10^{-11} \\text{ 米}^3/\\text{（千克·秒}^2\\text{）}$，地球半径$R_e=6.4 \\times 10^6 \\text{ 米}$，地球质量$M_e=6.0 \\times 10^{24} \\text{ 千克}$。忽略空气阻力。",
"problem_text_en": "[133] A missile is launched from the North Pole and lands on the equator (traversing 90° of latitude). Find the energy-optimal launch speed. Gravitational constant $G=6.67 \\times 10^{-11} \\text{ m}^3/\\text{kg·s}^2$, Earth's radius $R_e=6.4 \\times 10^6 \\text{ m}$, Earth's mass $M_e=6.0 \\times 10^{24} \\text{ kg}$. Neglect air resistance.",
"problem_img": ["133_1.png", "133_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["133_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["导弹椭圆轨道示意图（图133_1）；发射速度推导（图133_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Elliptical orbit of the missile (Figure 133_1); derivation of launch speed (Figure 133_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】如图133_1所示，图中A点是北极发射点，B点为导弹落地点，在赤道上。导弹在地球外部空间的轨道是椭圆轨道的一部分。根据对称性，椭圆长轴MN是直角$\\angle AoB$的角平分线。\n\n导弹在地球引力场中按椭圆轨道运动，机械能为：\n$$E = -G\\frac{M_e m}{2a}$$\n为使能量取最小值，应取最小的半长轴$a$值。\n\n设椭圆轨道的两焦点在$F_1$和$F_2$处，其中$F_1$必在地球中心。因北极发射点A在椭圆轨道上，依椭圆的性质，有：\n$$\\overline{AF_1} + \\overline{AF_2} = 2a$$\n其中$\\overline{AF_1}=R_e$，所以只有当$\\overline{AF_2}$取最小值时，$a$才是最小值。在MN上的$F_2$满足$AF_2 \\perp F_1F_2$时，$AF_2$即为最小值。由图中可知：\n$$2a = R_e + \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}R_e = \\frac{1}{2}R_e(2+\\sqrt{2})$$\n$$a = \\frac{1}{4}R_e(2+\\sqrt{2})$$\n\n利用A点处机械能的表达式：\n$$\\frac{1}{2}mv_A^2 - G\\frac{M_e m}{R_e} = -G\\frac{M_e m}{2a} = -G\\frac{M_e m}{2R_e} \\cdot \\frac{4}{2+\\sqrt{2}}$$\n解得：\n$$v_A^2 = \\frac{GM_e}{R_e}2(\\sqrt{2}-1)$$\n\n所以能量最省的发射速度为：\n$$v_{\\min} = \\sqrt{\\frac{GM_e}{R_e}2(\\sqrt{2}-1)} \\approx 7.20 \\times 10^3 \\text{ m/s}$$\n",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] The missile follows an elliptical orbit from the North Pole (A) to the equator (B). By symmetry, the major axis of the ellipse bisects $\\angle AOB$. The mechanical energy of the missile is $E = -G\\frac{M_e m}{2a}$, so minimizing energy requires minimizing the semi-major axis $a$.\n\nUsing the ellipse property $\\overline{AF_1} + \\overline{AF_2} = 2a$ (where $F_1$ is Earth's center), we find $2a = R_e + \\frac{\\sqrt{2}}{2}R_e$, giving $a = \\frac{R_e(2+\\sqrt{2})}{4}$. Substituting into the energy equation at point A:\n$$\\frac{1}{2}mv_A^2 - G\\frac{M_e m}{R_e} = -G\\frac{M_e m}{2a}$$\nSolving for $v_A$ yields:\n$$v_{\\min} = \\sqrt{\\frac{2GM_e(\\sqrt{2}-1)}{R_e}} \\approx 7.20 \\times 10^3 \\text{ m/s}$$\n",
"problem_answer": "能量最省的发射速度约为$7.20 \\times 10^3 \\text{ m/s}$（约$7.2 \\text{ km/s}$）。",
"difficulty": "4",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}

{
"problem_id": "134",
"problem_text_cn": "【134】这里讨论一个不带动力的宇宙航行器，去瞄准并命中一个遥远的行星（设为静止）问题。若用望远镜观察行星，其形状像一个圆盘，这个圆盘的面积为$\\pi R^2$，$R$是行星的半径。倘若引力不起作用，那么应把宇宙航行器对准这个面积，即能命中此行星。可是，宇宙航行器一路上将受行星引力吸引，情况将更有利于命中行星。引力将倾向于使航行器向着行星偏转，使得某些没有对准这个面积（$\\pi R^2$）的轨道也会有机会命中行星。结果是，命中行星的有效面积$A_e$大于行星的几何截面积$A_g=\\pi R^2$。$A_e$被称为行星的俘获截面。我们的问题就是要求出$A_e$。（计算中忽略太阳和其它行星的影响）",
"problem_text_en": "[134] Consider an unpowered spacecraft aiming to hit a distant, stationary planet. Without gravity, the spacecraft must target the planet's geometric cross-section $A_g = \\pi R^2$ to hit it. However, gravitational attraction deflects the spacecraft, increasing the effective target area $A_e$ (the capture cross-section). Find $A_e$. (Neglect the Sun and other planets.)",
"problem_img": ["134_1.png", "134_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["134_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["航行器偏转轨道示意图（图134_1）；俘获截面推导（图134_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Deflected orbits of the spacecraft (Figure 134_1); derivation of capture cross-section (Figure 134_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】如图134_1所示，为航行器命中行星的几个可能的轨道。由于航行器的发射点远离靶标行星，即这个距离远大于行星半径$R$，以致两者间作用力十分微弱，图中几个不同轨道开始实际上是互相平行的，起始轨道与图中$aa$线间距离$b$称为轨道的瞄准距离。我们只需求出航行器能够命中行星的最大$b$值。于是，能够命中行星的轨道必须通过的面积为：\n$$A_e = \\pi b^2$$\n\n如图134_2所示，$r\\sin\\varphi = b$，并利用初条件，$r\\to\\infty$，$v=v_0$（$v_0$为航行器射入时的初速度）。由机械能和角动量守恒：\n$$\\frac{1}{2}mv_0^2 = \\frac{1}{2}m[v(R)]^2 - G\\frac{Mm}{R}$$\n$$mbv_0 = mRv(R)$$\n\n联立消去$v(R)$，解得：\n$$b^2 = R^2\\left(1 + \\frac{GMm/R}{\\frac{1}{2}mv_0^2}\\right)$$\n\n命中行星的有效面积为：\n$$A_e = \\pi R^2\\left(1 + \\frac{GMm/R}{\\frac{1}{2}mv_0^2}\\right) = \\pi R^2\\left(1 - \\frac{U(R)}{E}\\right)$$\n其中$U(R) = -\\dfrac{GMm}{R}$。\n\n如果“去掉”引力，$U(R)\\to0$，$A_e=\\pi R^2$；如果$E\\to0$，$A_e\\to\\infty$，这意味着航行器从静止出发，将不可避免地会落到行星上去。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] The spacecraft's trajectory is deflected by the planet's gravity, so the maximum impact parameter $b$ determines the capture cross-section $A_e = \\pi b^2$. Using conservation of mechanical energy and angular momentum:\n$$\\frac{1}{2}mv_0^2 = \\frac{1}{2}m[v(R)]^2 - G\\frac{Mm}{R}$$\n$$mbv_0 = mRv(R)$$\n\nSolving for $b$ gives:\n$$b^2 = R^2\\left(1 + \\frac{2GM}{Rv_0^2}\\right)$$\n\nThus, the capture cross-section is:\n$$A_e = \\pi R^2\\left(1 + \\frac{2GM}{Rv_0^2}\\right)$$\n",
"problem_answer": "行星的俘获截面为$A_e = \\pi R^2\\left(1 + \\dfrac{2GM}{Rv_0^2}\\right)$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}

{
"problem_id": "135",
"problem_text_cn": "【135】有一群质量为$m$的质点，它们运动在具有公共中心的各个圆轨道上，每个粒子具有相同的动能。如果存在的力只是相互间的牛顿引力，求粒子数密度与离中心距离$r$之间的函数关系（假设密度是球对称的）。",
"problem_text_en": "[135] A group of particles of mass $m$ move in circular orbits around a common center, each with the same kinetic energy. If the only force is Newtonian gravity between particles, find the number density of particles as a function of distance $r$ from the center (assuming spherical symmetry).",
"problem_img": ["135_1.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["135_2.png"],
"img_cn": ["球对称引力系统示意图（图135_1）。"],
"img_en": ["Spherically symmetric gravitational system (Figure 135_1)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】由于每个粒子作绕公共中心的圆轨道运动，且质量密度相对于公共中心是球对称的，所以，若此粒子圆轨道半径为$r$，则将受到以公共中心为球心，$r$为半径的球形空间内质量$M(r)$的引力（方向指向中心），相当于$M(r)$集中在中心的一个质点对$m$的引力。而且，此粒子的动能$T$（题中告知动能为常量）在圆运动下等于总机械能的负值，即：\n$$T = \\frac{GM(r)m}{2r}$$\n则：\n$$M(r) = \\frac{2Tr}{Gm}$$\n\n由于密度（质量密度或粒子数密度）是球对称的，设质量密度为$\\rho(r)$，于是在$r\\to r+\\Delta r$范围内的粒子质量之和为：\n$$\\Delta M(r) = 4\\pi r^2\\rho(r)\\Delta r$$\n\n于是：\n$$\\rho(r) = \\frac{1}{4\\pi r^2}\\frac{\\Delta M}{\\Delta r} = \\frac{1}{4\\pi r^2}\\frac{2T}{Gm} = \\frac{T}{2\\pi Gm r^2}$$\n\n此处已应用$M(r) = \\dfrac{2Tr}{Gm}$。$\\rho(r)$是单位体积中的质量，所以单位体积中的粒子数$n(r)$为：\n$$n(r) = \\frac{\\rho(r)}{m} = \\frac{T}{2\\pi Gm^2 r^2}$$\n",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Each particle orbits the center in a circle, with gravitational force from the enclosed mass $M(r)$. For circular motion, kinetic energy equals the negative of total mechanical energy:\n$$T = \\frac{GM(r)m}{2r} \\implies M(r) = \\frac{2Tr}{Gm}$$\n\nThe mass density $\\rho(r)$ is related to $M(r)$ by $\\Delta M(r) = 4\\pi r^2\\rho(r)\\Delta r$, so:\n$$\\rho(r) = \\frac{T}{2\\pi Gm r^2}$$\n\nThe number density $n(r)$ (particles per unit volume) is:\n$$n(r) = \\frac{\\rho(r)}{m} = \\frac{T}{2\\pi Gm^2 r^2}$$\n",
"problem_answer": "粒子数密度与距离的关系为$n(r) = \\dfrac{T}{2\\pi Gm^2 r^2}$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}
{
"problem_id": "136",
"problem_text_cn": "【136】宇宙飞行器和小行星都绕太阳在同一平面内作圆周运动，飞行器的质量比小行星的质量小得很多，飞行器的速率为$v_0$，小行星的轨道半径为飞行器轨道半径的6倍。有人企图借助飞行器与小行星的碰撞使飞行器飞出太阳系，于是他便设计了如下方案：1)当飞行器在其圆周轨道的适当位置时，突然点燃飞行器上的喷气发动机，经过极短时间后立即关闭发动机，使飞行器获得所需的速度，沿圆周轨道的切线方向离开圆轨道；2)飞行器到达小行星的轨道时正好位于小行星的前缘，速度的方向和小行星在该处速度的方向相同，正好可被小行星碰撞；3)小行星与飞行器的碰撞是弹性正碰。不计燃烧的燃料质量。（ⅰ）试通过计算证明按上述方案能使飞行器飞出太阳系；（ⅱ）设在上述方案中，飞行器从发动机取得的能量为$E_1$。如果不采取上述方案而是令飞行器在圆轨道上突然点燃喷气发动机，经过极短时间后立即关闭发动机，使飞行器获得足够的速度沿圆轨道切线方向离开圆轨道后能直接飞出太阳系。采用这种办法时，飞行器从发动机取得的能量的最小值用$E_2$表示。问$\\dfrac{E_1}{E_2}$为多少？",
"problem_text_en": "[136] A spacecraft and an asteroid orbit the Sun in the same plane, with the spacecraft's mass much smaller than the asteroid's. The spacecraft's speed is $v_0$, and the asteroid's orbital radius is 6 times that of the spacecraft. A plan is proposed to use an elastic collision with the asteroid to eject the spacecraft from the Solar System: (1) The spacecraft's engine is briefly fired to boost its speed tangentially out of its circular orbit. (2) The spacecraft arrives at the asteroid's orbit just ahead of the asteroid, with velocity aligned to the asteroid's. (3) An elastic head-on collision occurs. Neglect fuel mass. (i) Prove the spacecraft escapes the Solar System. (ii) Let $E_1$ be the energy from the engine for the collision scheme, and $E_2$ be the minimum energy for direct escape. Find $\\dfrac{E_1}{E_2}$.",
"problem_img": ["136_1.png", "136_2.png", "136_3.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["136_4.png"],
"img_cn": ["霍曼转移轨道与碰撞示意图（图136_1）；轨道速度计算（图136_2）；能量对比分析（图136_3）。"],
"img_en": ["Hohmann transfer orbit and collision diagram (Figure 136_1); orbital velocity calculation (Figure 136_2); energy comparison analysis (Figure 136_3)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】（ⅰ）设太阳质量为$M_0$，飞行器质量为$m$，轨道半径为$R$。飞行器沿半椭圆轨道到达小行星轨道（半径$6R$），由开普勒第二定律：\n$$u_0 R = u \\cdot 6R$$\n能量守恒：\n$$\\frac{1}{2}mu_0^2 - \\frac{GM_0 m}{R} = \\frac{1}{2}mu^2 - \\frac{GM_0 m}{6R}$$\n结合圆轨道速度$v_0 = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{GM_0}{R}}$，解得：\n$$u_0 = \\sqrt{\\frac{12}{7}}v_0,\\quad u = \\sqrt{\\frac{1}{21}}v_0$$\n小行星轨道速度：\n$$V = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{GM_0}{6R}} = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{1}{6}}v_0$$\n因$V > u$，碰撞后飞行器相对太阳速度为：\n$$u_1 = 2V - u = \\left(\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2}{3}} - \\sqrt{\\dfrac{1}{21}}\\right)v_0$$\n小行星轨道的逃逸速度为：\n$$u_2 = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2GM_0}{6R}} = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{1}{3}}v_0$$\n显然$u_1 > u_2$，故飞行器能飞出太阳系。\n\n（ⅱ）$E_1 = \\dfrac{1}{2}m(u_0^2 - v_0^2) = \\dfrac{5}{14}mv_0^2$\n直接逃逸速度$u_3 = \\sqrt{2}v_0$，故$E_2 = \\dfrac{1}{2}m(u_3^2 - v_0^2) = \\dfrac{1}{2}mv_0^2$\n因此：\n$$\\dfrac{E_1}{E_2} = \\dfrac{5/14}{1/2} = \\dfrac{5}{7} \\approx 0.71$$\n",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] (i) Using Kepler's second law and energy conservation for the elliptical transfer orbit, we find the spacecraft's velocity at the asteroid's orbit is $u = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{1}{21}}v_0$, while the asteroid's velocity is $V = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{1}{6}}v_0$. After elastic collision, the spacecraft's velocity is $u_1 = 2V - u > \\sqrt{\\dfrac{1}{3}}v_0$ (the escape velocity from the asteroid's orbit), confirming escape.\n\n(ii) $E_1 = \\dfrac{5}{14}mv_0^2$ and $E_2 = \\dfrac{1}{2}mv_0^2$, so $\\dfrac{E_1}{E_2} = \\dfrac{5}{7} \\approx 0.71$.",
"problem_answer": "（ⅰ）碰撞后飞行器速度大于小行星轨道的逃逸速度，能飞出太阳系；（ⅱ）$\\dfrac{E_1}{E_2} = \\dfrac{5}{7} \\approx 0.71$。",
"difficulty": "4",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}

{
"problem_id": "137",
"problem_text_cn": "【137】一双星系统，两颗星的质量分别为$M$和$m$（设$M>m$），距离为$d$，在引力作用下绕不动质心作圆周运动。设这两颗星近似为质点。在超新星爆炸中，质量为$M$的星体损失质量$\\Delta M$。假设爆炸是瞬时的、球对称的，并且对残余体不施加任何作用力（或作用力抵消），对另一颗星也无直接作用。试求，在什么条件下，余下的新的双星系统仍被约束而不相互远离。",
"problem_text_en": "[137] A binary star system consists of stars of mass $M$ and $m$ ($M>m$) separated by $d$, orbiting their common center of mass. In a supernova explosion, star $M$ loses mass $\\Delta M$ instantaneously and spherically, with no force on the remnant or the other star. Find the condition for the new system to remain bound (not fly apart).",
"problem_img": ["137_1.png", "137_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["137_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["双星系统质心运动示意图（图137_1）；爆炸后机械能分析（图137_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Binary system center-of-mass motion (Figure 137_1); post-explosion mechanical energy analysis (Figure 137_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】原系统机械能小于零（束缚态）。爆炸后，新系统的质心系机械能需仍小于零。原角速度：\n$$\\omega^2 = \\dfrac{G(M+m)}{d^3}$$\n新系统势能：\n$$E_p = -\\dfrac{G(M-\\Delta M)m}{d}$$\n质心系动能：\n$$E_k = \\dfrac{1}{2}\\dfrac{(M-\\Delta M)m}{M-\\Delta M+m}\\omega^2 d^2$$\n代入$\\omega^2$并化简，束缚条件为：\n$$E_p + E_k < 0 \\implies \\Delta M < \\dfrac{1}{2}(M+m)$$\n",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] The original system is bound (negative mechanical energy). After the explosion, the new system remains bound if its center-of-mass mechanical energy is negative. The angular velocity is $\\omega^2 = \\dfrac{G(M+m)}{d^3}$. Substituting into the energy condition, we find:\n$$\\Delta M < \\dfrac{1}{2}(M+m)$$\n",
"problem_answer": "新双星系统保持束缚的条件为$\\Delta M < \\dfrac{1}{2}(M+m)$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}

{
"problem_id": "138",
"problem_text_cn": "【6-1】在光滑的水平桌面上，一个质量为$m$的质点系于一根原长为$a$的轻橡皮绳的一端，橡皮绳的另一端系于桌面上一固定点$o$。橡皮绳拉伸时的劲度系数为$k$。若质点在开始时被拉至距$o$点距离为$2a$处，并给质点在垂直于橡皮绳方向以初速度$V$。1)为使质点绕$o$点作圆周运动，求$V$的大小；2)为使橡皮绳不松弛，$V$的最小值$V_m$为多大？3)当$0<V<V_m$时，质点在运动中距$o$点的最小距离$r_m$为多大？",
"problem_text_en": "[6-1] A particle of mass $m$ is attached to a light elastic cord (natural length $a$, spring constant $k$) fixed at point $o$ on a smooth horizontal table. The particle is pulled to $2a$ from $o$ and given an initial velocity $V$ perpendicular to the cord. (1) Find $V$ for circular motion about $o$. (2) Find the minimum $V_m$ to keep the cord taut. (3) Find the minimum distance $r_m$ when $0<V<V_m$.",
"problem_img": ["138_1.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["138_2.png"],
"img_cn": ["橡皮绳约束质点运动示意图（图138_1）。"],
"img_en": ["Particle motion constrained by an elastic cord (Figure 138_1)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】1) 圆周运动半径$2a$，向心力由橡皮绳弹力提供：\n$$k(2a-a) = m\\dfrac{V^2}{2a} \\implies V = a\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2k}{m}}$$\n\n2) 绳不松弛的临界情况是最近距离为$a$，此时角动量守恒$2aV_m = av$，机械能守恒：\n$$\\dfrac{1}{2}mV_m^2 + \\dfrac{1}{2}ka^2 = \\dfrac{1}{2}mv^2$$\n解得：\n$$V_m = a\\sqrt{\\dfrac{k}{3m}}$$\n\n3) 当$0<V<V_m$时，绳松弛后质点做匀速直线运动，角动量守恒$2aV = r_m v$，机械能守恒：\n$$\\dfrac{1}{2}mV^2 + \\dfrac{1}{2}ka^2 = \\dfrac{1}{2}mv^2$$\n解得：\n$$r_m = \\dfrac{2Va}{\\sqrt{V^2 + \\dfrac{k}{m}a^2}}$$\n",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] 1) For circular motion at radius $2a$, the elastic force provides centripetal acceleration:\n$$k(2a-a) = m\\dfrac{V^2}{2a} \\implies V = a\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2k}{m}}$$\n\n2) To keep the cord taut, the minimum distance is $a$. Using angular momentum and energy conservation:\n$$V_m = a\\sqrt{\\dfrac{k}{3m}}$$\n\n3) When $0<V<V_m$, the cord goes slack, and the particle moves uniformly. Solving conservation laws gives:\n$$r_m = \\dfrac{2Va}{\\sqrt{V^2 + \\dfrac{k}{m}a^2}}$$\n",
"problem_answer": "1) $V = a\\sqrt{\\dfrac{2k}{m}}$；2) $V_m = a\\sqrt{\\dfrac{k}{3m}}$；3) $r_m = \\dfrac{2Va}{\\sqrt{V^2 + \\dfrac{k}{m}a^2}}$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}

{
"problem_id": "139",
"problem_text_cn": "【6-3】一质量为$m$的质点处在一光滑的水平面上，用一不可伸长细绳连着穿过一光滑小孔$o$而悬挂的质量为$M$的物体。开始时使$m$距孔$o$的距离为$a$，且有一垂直于绳的速度$v$，如图6-例3所示。试求当$m$再次运动到速度方向与绳垂直时，它离小孔的距离$x$。",
"problem_text_en": "[6-3] A particle of mass $m$ on a smooth horizontal table is connected via an inextensible cord through a smooth hole $o$ to a hanging mass $M$. Initially, $m$ is at distance $a$ from $o$ with velocity $v$ perpendicular to the cord. Find the distance $x$ when $m$ next has velocity perpendicular to the cord.",
"problem_img": ["139_1.png", "139_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["139_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["小孔约束质点运动示意图（图139_1）；能量与角动量守恒推导（图139_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Particle motion constrained by a hole (Figure 139_1); energy and angular momentum conservation derivation (Figure 139_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】系统机械能守恒：\n$$\\dfrac{1}{2}mv'^2 = \\dfrac{1}{2}mv^2 + Mg(a-x)$$\n对小孔的角动量守恒：\n$$mxv' = mav \\implies v' = \\dfrac{av}{x}$$\n代入机械能方程并整理，解得正根：\n$$x = \\dfrac{mv^2}{4Mg} + \\dfrac{1}{2}\\sqrt{\\dfrac{mv^2}{2Mg}\\left(\\dfrac{mv^2}{2Mg} + 4a\\right)}$$\n",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Using conservation of mechanical energy and angular momentum about the hole:\n$$\\dfrac{1}{2}mv'^2 = \\dfrac{1}{2}mv^2 + Mg(a-x),\\quad mxv' = mav$$\nSolving these gives:\n$$x = \\dfrac{mv^2}{4Mg} + \\dfrac{1}{2}\\sqrt{\\dfrac{mv^2}{2Mg}\\left(\\dfrac{mv^2}{2Mg} + 4a\\right)}$$\n",
"problem_answer": "再次垂直时的距离为$x = \\dfrac{mv^2}{4Mg} + \\dfrac{1}{2}\\sqrt{\\dfrac{mv^2}{2Mg}\\left(\\dfrac{mv^2}{2Mg} + 4a\\right)}$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
}
