"problem_text_en": "[154] A uniform rod rests in a hemispherical bowl (in a vertical plane through the center). The central angle subtended by the rod at the center is $2\\alpha$, and the coefficient of static friction is $\\mu=\\tan\\beta$. Prove the maximum angle between the rod and the horizontal is $\\theta = \\arctg\\left[\\dfrac{\\tan(\\alpha+\\beta)-\\tan(\\alpha-\\beta)}{2}\\right]$.",
"problem_img": ["154_1.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["154_2.png"],
"img_cn": ["直棒在半球碗中的受力分析（图154_1）；几何关系推导（图154_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Force analysis of the rod in the hemispherical bowl (Figure 154_1); geometric relation derivation (Figure 154_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】临界状态下，直棒两端摩擦力与支持力的合力与法线夹角为$\\beta$，三力汇交于一点。利用几何关系得：\n$$\\tan\\theta = \\dfrac{\\overline{CD}}{\\overline{o'D}} = \\dfrac{1}{2}\\left[\\tan(\\alpha+\\beta) - \\tan(\\alpha-\\beta)\\right]$$\n因此：\n$$\\theta = \\arctg\\left[\\dfrac{\\tan(\\alpha+\\beta)-\\tan(\\alpha-\\beta)}{2}\\right]$$\n得证。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] At the critical state, the resultant of friction and normal force at each end makes an angle $\\beta$ with the normal, and the three forces concur. Using geometry:\n$$\\tan\\theta = \\dfrac{1}{2}\\left[\\tan(\\alpha+\\beta) - \\tan(\\alpha-\\beta)\\right]$$\nThus:\n$$\\theta = \\arctg\\left[\\dfrac{\\tan(\\alpha+\\beta)-\\tan(\\alpha-\\beta)}{2}\\right]$$\nQED.",
"problem_answer": "证明成立：$\\theta = \\arctg\\left[\\dfrac{\\tan(\\alpha+\\beta)-\\tan(\\alpha-\\beta)}{2}\\right]$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
},
{
"problem_id": "155",
"problem_text_cn": "【155】倾角为$\\theta$的楔置于水平地面上，楔的斜面上放一物块$A$，物块与斜面之间的静摩擦系数和滑动摩擦系数均为$\\mu$。开始时，楔静止，物块$A$静止在斜面上，且离地面高度为$h$。现让楔以恒加速度$a$沿水平面向右运动，求：1)加速度$a$在什么范围内，才能使物块$A$沿斜面滑下？2)设加速度$a$在上面求得的范围内，求物块$A$从楔开始运动起经多长时间落到水平地面上？",
"problem_text_en": "[155] A wedge of angle $\\theta$ rests on a horizontal table. A block $A$ is placed on its inclined surface, with coefficient of friction $\\mu$. Initially, both are stationary, and the block is at height $h$. The wedge accelerates horizontally to the right at constant acceleration $a$. (1) Find the range of $a$ for the block to slide down the wedge. (2) Find the time for the block to reach the ground.",
"problem_img": ["155_1.png", "155_2.png", "155_3.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["155_4.png"],
"img_cn": ["楔与物块系统示意图（图155_1）；临界加速度分析（图155_2）；相对加速度计算（图155_3）。"],
"img_en": ["Wedge and block system diagram (Figure 155_1); critical acceleration analysis (Figure 155_2); relative acceleration calculation (Figure 155_3)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】\n1. **下滑条件**：物块不脱离斜面且向下滑动，故：\n$$g\\dfrac{\\mu-\\tan\\theta}{1+\\mu\\tan\\theta} < a \\leq g\\cot\\theta$$\n2. **下落时间**：相对加速度$a' = g\\sin\\theta + a\\cos\\theta - \\mu(g\\cos\\theta - a\\sin\\theta)$，斜面长度$L = \\dfrac{h}{\\sin\\theta}$，由$L = \\dfrac{1}{2}a't^2$得：\n$$t = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2h}{\\sin\\theta\\left[a(\\cos\\theta+\\mu\\sin\\theta)+g(\\sin\\theta-\\mu\\cos\\theta)\\right]}}$$",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution]\n1. **Sliding condition**: The block slides down without losing contact:\n$$g\\dfrac{\\mu-\\tan\\theta}{1+\\mu\\tan\\theta} < a \\leq g\\cot\\theta$$\n2. **Time to fall**: Relative acceleration $a' = g\\sin\\theta + a\\cos\\theta - \\mu(g\\cos\\theta - a\\sin\\theta)$. The length of the incline is $L = \\dfrac{h}{\\sin\\theta}$, so:\n$$t = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2h}{\\sin\\theta\\left[a(\\cos\\theta+\\mu\\sin\\theta)+g(\\sin\\theta-\\mu\\cos\\theta)\\right]}}$$",
"problem_answer": "1) 加速度范围为$g\\dfrac{\\mu-\\tan\\theta}{1+\\mu\\tan\\theta} < a \\leq g\\cot\\theta$；2) 下落时间为$t = \\sqrt{\\dfrac{2h}{\\sin\\theta\\left[a(\\cos\\theta+\\mu\\sin\\theta)+g(\\sin\\theta-\\mu\\cos\\theta)\\right]}}$。",
"difficulty": "4",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
},
{
"problem_id": "156",
"problem_text_cn": "【156】在水平杆$MN$上套上两小环$A$和$B$，一长为$l$的不可伸长的细线两端分别系在环$A$、$B$上，并在细线中点挂一质量为$M$的物块$C$。设$A$、$B$环与杆间的静摩擦系数为$\\mu$。若两小环质量忽略不计，求系统达静平衡时小环$A$、$B$间的最大距离$x$。",
"problem_text_en": "[156] Two small rings $A$ and $B$ slide on a horizontal rod $MN$, connected by an inextensible string of length $l$ with a mass $M$ hanging at the midpoint. The coefficient of static friction between the rings and the rod is $\\mu$. Find the maximum distance between $A$ and $B$ in equilibrium, neglecting the rings' mass.",
"problem_img": ["156_1.png", "156_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["156_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["环与细线系统示意图（图156_1）；受力分析与平衡条件（图156_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Ring and string system diagram (Figure 156_1); force analysis and equilibrium conditions (Figure 156_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】设绳与杆夹角为$\\varphi$，张力$T$，则$2T\\cos\\varphi = Mg$。对环受力分析，最大静摩擦力$f = \\mu N = T\\sin\\varphi$，解得：\n$$\\tan\\varphi = \\mu\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)$$\n因此最大距离：\n$$x = l\\sin\\varphi = \\dfrac{\\mu l\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu^2\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)^2}}$$\n当$m=0$时，$x = \\dfrac{\\mu l}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu^2}}$。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Let the string make an angle $\\varphi$ with the rod, and tension $T$. Then $2T\\cos\\varphi = Mg$. Force balance on the ring gives $f = \\mu N = T\\sin\\varphi$, so:\n$$\\tan\\varphi = \\mu\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)$$\nThe maximum distance is:\n$$x = \\dfrac{\\mu l\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu^2\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)^2}}$$\nFor $m=0$, $x = \\dfrac{\\mu l}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu^2}}$.",
"problem_answer": "最大距离为$x = \\dfrac{\\mu l\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu^2\\left(1+\\dfrac{2m}{M}\\right)^2}}$（当$m=0$时$x = \\dfrac{\\mu l}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu^2}}$）。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
},
{
"problem_id": "157",
"problem_text_cn": "【157】质量为$m$的物体静止于倾角为$\\theta$的固定斜面上，物体与斜面之间的滑动摩擦系数为$\\mu_k$。试问在下列两种情况下，要使物体匀速滑动，至少要加多大的外力以及这个外力的方向：1)向下滑动；2)向上滑动。",
"problem_text_en": "[157] A mass $m$ rests on a fixed incline of angle $\\theta$, with coefficient of kinetic friction $\\mu_k$. Find the minimum external force and its direction to make the object slide uniformly: (1) downward; (2) upward.",
"problem_img": ["157_1.png", "157_2.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["157_3.png"],
"img_cn": ["斜面上物体受力分析（图157_1）；最小外力推导（图157_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Force analysis of the object on the incline (Figure 157_1); minimum external force derivation (Figure 157_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】\n1. **向下滑动**：\n   - 若$\\mu_k > \\tan\\theta$，最小力$T_{\\min} = mg\\dfrac{\\mu_k\\cos\\theta-\\sin\\theta}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$，方向与斜面成$\\arctan\\mu_k$角。\n   - 若$\\mu_k < \\tan\\theta$，最小力$T_{\\min} = mg\\dfrac{\\sin\\theta-\\mu_k\\cos\\theta}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$，方向与斜面成$\\arctan\\mu_k$角（反向）。\n2. **向上滑动**：\n   - 最小力$T_{\\min} = mg\\dfrac{\\mu_k\\cos\\theta+\\sin\\theta}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$，方向与斜面成$\\arctan\\mu_k$角。\n   - 当$\\mu_k \\geq \\cot\\theta$时，$T_{\\min} = mg$（竖直向上）。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution]\n1. **Downward sliding**:\n   - If $\\mu_k > \\tan\\theta$, $T_{\\min} = mg\\dfrac{\\mu_k\\cos\\theta-\\sin\\theta}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$, direction at $\\arctan\\mu_k$ to the incline.\n   - If $\\mu_k < \\tan\\theta$, $T_{\\min} = mg\\dfrac{\\sin\\theta-\\mu_k\\cos\\theta}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$, direction at $\\arctan\\mu_k$ to the incline (opposite).\n2. **Upward sliding**:\n   - $T_{\\min} = mg\\dfrac{\\mu_k\\cos\\theta+\\sin\\theta}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$, direction at $\\arctan\\mu_k$ to the incline.\n   - If $\\mu_k \\geq \\cot\\theta$, $T_{\\min} = mg$ (vertically upward).",
"problem_answer": "1) 向下滑动时，最小力为$mg\\dfrac{|\\mu_k\\cos\\theta-\\sin\\theta|}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$，方向与斜面成$\\arctan\\mu_k$角；2) 向上滑动时，最小力为$mg\\dfrac{\\mu_k\\cos\\theta+\\sin\\theta}{\\sqrt{1+\\mu_k^2}}$（或$mg$当$\\mu_k \\geq \\cot\\theta$时）。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
},
