"problem_text_en": "[162] A container of depth $H$ is filled with liquid whose density increases linearly from $\\rho_0$ at the surface to $\\rho$ at the bottom. Two balls of volume $V$ (densities $\\rho_1$, $\\rho_2$) are connected by an inextensible string of length $l$. Find the tension in the string when the system is stationary.",
"problem_img": ["162_1.png", "162_2.png"],
