{
"problem_id": "163",
"problem_text_cn": "【163】如图7-练18所示，容器中盛有密度为$\\rho_0$的液体，并放有一种体积为$V$，密度为$\\rho$的物块。图(a)中物体浮于液体表面，图(b)中物体被一根绳子连结在容器底部，使物块淹没在液体之中。假设两种情况都让容器以加速度$a$竖直向上运动。问：1)图(a)中物块将如何运动？2)图(b)中物块与容器底部相连的绳子中张力为多大？（设$\\rho_0>\\rho$）",
"problem_text_en": "[163] A container holds liquid of density $\\rho_0$ and a block of volume $V$ and density $\\rho$ ($\\rho_0>\\rho$). In (a), the block floats; in (b), it is submerged and tied to the bottom. The container accelerates upward at $a$. (1) How does the block move in (a)? (2) Find the tension in the string in (b).",
"problem_img": ["163_1.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["163_2.png"],
"img_cn": ["物块在加速容器中的受力分析（图163_1）；张力推导（图163_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Force analysis of the block in an accelerating container (Figure 163_1); tension derivation (Figure 163_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】\n1. **图(a)中运动情况**：在容器参考系中，物块视重为$m(g+a)$，排开液体视重为$\\rho_0(g+a)V'$。由$m(g+a)=\\rho_0(g+a)V'$得$V'=\\dfrac{m}{\\rho_0}$，与静止时相同，故物块相对液面无运动。\n2. **图(b)中张力**：静止时张力$T_0=\\rho_0gV-\\rho gV$。加速时张力为：\n$$T=\\rho_0(g+a)V-\\rho(g+a)V=T_0\\left(1+\\dfrac{a}{g}\\right)$$",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution]\n1. **Motion in (a)** In the container frame, the apparent weight of the block is $m(g+a)$, and the apparent weight of displaced liquid is $\\rho_0(g+a)V'$. Since $V'=\\dfrac{m}{\\rho_0}$ (same as at rest), the block does not move relative to the liquid surface.\n2. **Tension in (b)** At rest, $T_0=\\rho_0gV-\\rho gV$. Under acceleration:\n$$T=T_0\\left(1+\\dfrac{a}{g}\\right)$$",
"problem_answer": "1) 物块相对液面不发生运动；2) 绳中张力为$T=T_0\\left(1+\\dfrac{a}{g}\\right)$，其中$T_0=\\rho_0gV-\\rho gV$。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
},
{
"problem_id": "164",
"problem_text_cn": "【164】如图7-练19(a)，杯中盛有密度均匀的混合液体，密度为$\\rho$。经过一段时间后变为密度分别为$\\rho_1$、$\\rho_2$（$\\rho_2>\\rho_1$）的两层均匀液体如图7-练19(b)。设总体积不变，则杯内底面所受的液体的压强是否有变化？若有变化，如何变化？试证明你的结论。",
"problem_text_en": "[164] A cup contains a uniform mixture of density $\\rho$, which separates into two layers of density $\\rho_1$ and $\\rho_2$ ($\\rho_2>\\rho_1$) with total volume unchanged. Does the pressure at the bottom of the cup change? If so, how? Prove your conclusion.",
"problem_img": ["164_1.png"],
"problem_img_process": ["164_2.png"],
"img_cn": ["液体分层前后的压强分析（图164_1）；体积与质量守恒推导（图164_2）。"],
"img_en": ["Pressure analysis before and after liquid separation (Figure 164_1); volume and mass conservation derivation (Figure 164_2)."],
"problem_solution_cn": "【分析与解】设原液面高度为$H$，分层后高度为$H_1$、$H_2$。由体积不变$H\\bar{S}=H_1\\bar{S}_1+H_2\\bar{S}_2$，质量不变$\\rho H\\bar{S}=\\rho_1H_1\\bar{S}_1+\\rho_2H_2\\bar{S}_2$，得：\n$$(\\rho-\\rho_1)H_1\\bar{S}_1=(\\rho_2-\\rho)H_2\\bar{S}_2$$\n因$\\bar{S}_1>\\bar{S}_2$，故$(\\rho_2-\\rho)H_2>(\\rho-\\rho_1)H_1$，即$\\rho_1H_1+\\rho_2H_2>\\rho H$。因此杯底压强：\n$$p_2=\\rho_1gH_1+\\rho_2gH_2>\\rho gH=p_1$$\n即压强变大。",
"problem_solution_en": "[Analysis and Solution] Let the original height be $H$, and heights after separation be $H_1$, $H_2$. Volume and mass conservation give:\n$$(\\rho-\\rho_1)H_1\\bar{S}_1=(\\rho_2-\\rho)H_2\\bar{S}_2$$\nSince $\\bar{S}_1>\\bar{S}_2$, we have $\\rho_1H_1+\\rho_2H_2>\\rho H$, so the bottom pressure increases:\n$$p_2>p_1$$",
"problem_answer": "杯底压强变大，证明如上。",
"difficulty": "3",
"problem_tags": ["Mechanics"]
},
{
"problem_id": "165",
"problem_text_cn": "【165】如图7-练20(a)所示的容器中，盛有密度为$\\rho$的液体，想像在此液体中有一个半径为$R$的球面，球心$o$离液面的深度为$H$。为讨论方便起见，设液面上受到的大气压为零。1)过球心$o$的一个水平截面把球面分成上、下两个半球面。求球面外的液体对上、下两个半球面的压力各为多大？2)在1)中所取水平截面上取一条直径，过此直径再作一截面，与水平截面交角为$\\theta$，如图7-练20(b)所示。这个截面把球面也分成两个半球面，求图中左上半球面上受到球外液体的压力。",
"problem_text_en": "[165] A container holds liquid of density $\\rho$, with a spherical surface of radius $R$ centered at depth $H$ (atmospheric pressure is zero). (1) A horizontal plane through the center divides the sphere into upper and lower hemispheres. Find the liquid pressure on each hemisphere. (2) A second plane through a diameter of the horizontal plane, at angle $\\theta$ to it, divides the sphere into two hemispheres. Find the pressure on the upper-left hemisphere.",
"problem_img": ["165_1.png", "165_2.png"],
